Create Stow Job (UNREGISTERED to STOCK with stockInformation)

request.description:
[https://fulfillmenttools.github.io/api-reference-ui/#/Inventory%20Management%20-%20Stowing/createStowJob](https://fulfillmenttools.github.io/api-reference-ui/#/Inventory%20Management%20-%20Stowing/createStowJob)

This request will create a stowjob with a single item which does not have stock at the moment. Hence the takeFrom type **UNREGISTERED** meaning that we want to book new stock into the system. We dont provide a stockRef for stowTo beacause we want to let the system create a new stock entity once the item is stowed (stowTo.stowed is filled with information). With the **stockInformation** field we define which properties the newly created stock will contain. If you already have a listing defined for the given tenantAerticleId these properties will be validated against its propertyDefinition. See also the [stock property documentation](https://docs.fulfillmenttools.com/api-docs/use-cases/inventory-management/entities/stock/stock-properties#setting-constraints-validation)
